      "side": 1,
      "message": "SkSampledCodec is how we create scaled down versions of images. It does a more complex version of the following:\n\n  codec-\u003estartIncrementalDecode(...);\n  auto* sampler \u003d codec-\u003egetSampler(true);\n  sampler-\u003esetSampleX(sampleX);\n  sampler-\u003esetSampleY(sampleY);\n  codec-\u003eincrementalDecode(\u0026rowsDecoded);\n\nIt actually has two ways of doing it - scanline decoding came first, and I think it\u0027s more straightforward. But it was incompatible with libpng\u0027s incremental decoding, so I came up with incrementalDecode to support both true incremental decoding and this sampled decode.\n\nPart of the goal of the sampled decode is to avoid allocating the buffer for the full sized image. But Wuffs allocates the full sized image anyway. So maybe we shouldn\u0027t even use SkSampledCodec. Instead, we could have another adapter like SkWebpAdapterCodec. It would decode each frame, and if the client wants a scale we can just use the drawing engine to draw the image with a scale.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 133,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 133,
        "endChar": 69
      },
      "revId": "8a250dc152e4a93801f77cbcb19c2e490656b67b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
